🤩Exciting news!! The Blue Canoe hopes to open for business soon! After a full renovation to the space and patio addition in the back, we hope to be a great place to come gather with friends and family while eating delicious fare made by Chef Drew Bonnet! We are so excited to have Chef Drew on our team and we’re sure you’re going to love his creations!! We will be a full bar with beer 🍺 on tap as well as offering mixed drinks 🍹 🍸 🍷 ! But don’t worry, it’s family friendly too - feel free to bring your kiddos in to eat. The kids menu is sure to please 😊

🤩More exciting news🤩We are hiring!! General Manager, shift managers for front of house, wait staff, bar tenders, cooks, dishwashers all needed! Please email bluecanoemelvern@gmail.com to find out more!

post_text:
Mowing season is in full swing! We would like to remind all property owners in Melvern of the City weed and vegetation ordinance. Ordinance No. 303 requires that no weeds or grass shall be over 12 inches tall. If you receive a Notice of Violation, after the required time has expired, the City can mow your property. The current rates are as follows:

Administration fee - $100.00

1 ft - 100 ft. total lot width - $100.00. Addition lot width is charged an additional $1.00 per foot.

Backhoe and operator - $150.00 per hour (1 hr. minimum)

Chainsaw and operator - $100.00 per hour (1 hr. minimum)

Tractor and bushog - $150.00 per hour (1 Hr. minimum)

post_text:
Are you ready to go on a Bear Hunt? Melvern is ready for a Bear Hunt! Some bears have made their way to our town and are waiting in windows to be counted by all - young and old alike! Hopefully, as our weather improves, children will be able to get outside, go for a walk and count how many bears are waiting to greet them! Please come out to enjoy the sunshine and fresh air while remembering social distancing and avoiding the playground.



If anyone is interested in joining this display of stuffed bears please do so. Just place the bears in a front window or door where they can be seen as some one walks by. If anyone would like to join but does not have a bear in their house or place of business, please contact Jane Yocum @ 549-3550. She has more bears and will be happy to deliver to you! Thank you to everyone for helping with this project for our youngest kids!

FYI Friends,
Starting tomorrow the Courthouse hours will be 8 a.m. to 1 p.m. We will take phone calls and appointments. The transfer station will remain open but all recycling is closed.

All offices have a box at the west door and a deputy is there to let people in.

Our job is to serve the public and that is what we are there to do. Please be patient with us as we work through this uncertain time.

Stay safe and stay well, we will all come through this together because we are better together.

Thank you for allowing me to use this forum to inform you.

Starting March 30, thru April 19, Kansas Governor Kelley has ordered all Kansans to stay at home to curb the spread of Covid-19, unless for essential activities, such as getting food or medical care.

PRACTICE SOCIAL DISTANCING
Walking your dog, working in your yard, going for walks, running necessary errands, and recreation, while maintaining social distance, and in groups of 10 or less is allowed. You can drive to essential services, but driving around for fun is out!

Shannon Patterson Bowers shared a post to the group: Melvern Sunflower Fair Days.
June 13, 2019 at 12:12 PM ·

We are only 1 week away from the 1st night of the 2019 Melvern Sunflower Fair Days!

Shannon Patterson Bowers‎Melvern Sunflower Fair Days
May 22, 2019 at 11:35 AM ·

Does your organization, church, school group, business, etc. need some extra money? If so, please plan to participate in the 2019 Melvern Sunflower Fair Days Parade!

The them for the 2019 Melvern Sunflower Fair Days Parade will be "Small Town USA - Redneck Jamboree!" We are super excited about seeing what you rednecks will come up with this year! We all know how to celebrate Small Town but how to incorporate it with a Redneck Jamboree puts it in a whole new light!

The Parade is always the highlight of the Sunflower Fair Days and we encourage everyone to start now and get a float together to have in the parade. Please join us in helping make this parade one of the best yet!

We will be giving $200 for 1st place float, $125 for 2nd place float and $75 for 3rd place float. Prizes will only be awarded to floats and all members participating MUST be on the float.

Ready, Set, Go!!!!

The them for the 2019 Melvern Sunflower Fair Days Parade will be "Small Town USA - Redneck Jamboree!" We are super excited about seeing what you rednecks will come up with this year! We all know how to celebrate Small Town but how to incorporate it with a Redneck Jamboree puts it in a whole new light!

The Parade is always the highlight of the Sunflower Fair Days and we encourage everyone to start now and get a float together to have in the parade. Please join us in helping make this parade one of the best yet!

We will be giving $200 for 1st place float, $125 for 2nd place float and $75 for 3rd place float. Prizes will only be awarded to floats and all members participating MUST be on the float.

Ready, Set, Go!!!!

post_text: We continue to receive complaints about dogs running at large within city limits. We ask all pet owners to please keep your dog on your property and under your control, as referenced in Ordinance No. 291, available at Melvern City Hall for review. We have recently had issues with individuals walking dogs on a leash, which is perfectly legal in Melvern, being confronted by a dog, or dogs, running at large. Please be a responsible pet owner!

post_text: Just to clarify - the new City Hall does have a secure records room. During regular business hours (Monday - Friday, 7:00 a.m. - 3:00 p.m.), in the event of severe weather, the room would be open to individuals seeking shelter, but it will not be open after regular hours. This is a secure storage room, and with the shelving and files located in it, it has minimal room for shelter.

post_text: We have recently had complaints about dogs running at large in town. With school out, and the weather warming up, we have children riding bicycles, people out walking, and generally more outside activities. Dogs running at large are becoming a problem. Please tag, and pen or leash your dog. Dog tags were due April 1. Any dog picked up without identification, will be taken to the pound and held for three days. If not claimed within three days, the animal may be destroyed. A dog with current tags can be returned to the owner when they are picked up. We love responsible pet owners!!!
